const title = "Hestan Appliance Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Hestan range, outdoor grill & refrigerator repair in LA. Same-day service, OEM parts. $89 diagnostic, waived with repair.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What Hestan appliances do you repair in Los Angeles?",
    a: "Hestan's residential lineup, primarily cooking and outdoor. Indoor: GROR-series ranges (30 / 36 / 48-inch dual-fuel and gas), HVBI ventilation hoods, indoor refrigeration columns. Outdoor: HOTR outdoor ranges, GMWR outdoor refrigerators, integrated outdoor cooking suites. Hestan residential focuses on cooking and outdoor — there's no Hestan laundry, and the dishwasher work that occasionally comes up is on the newer additions to the lineup. Hestan also runs a separate commercial division (Hestan Commercial Corporation, the 40-year-old parent) that supplies restaurants — different scope, different parts ecosystem; on the residential side we work the Hestan Smart Cooking lineup launched 2015 and the outdoor product released through the same brand."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does Hestan repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when you approve the work. Hestan repair pricing sits in the upper-luxury tier — comparable to Wolf or Thermador, reflecting hand-built construction and US-based parts supply. Common Hestan service items: ceramic burner igniter $185-$285 per zone; spark module $265-$405; convection fan motor on GROR ranges $345-$525 (the GROR convection fan is the most common 2018-2021 cohort failure — see year-pattern below); oven thermostat $265-$405; bake / broil element $245-$385; HVBI ventilation blower motor $385-$580; smart-control electronic module $385-$580 (Hestan's connected platform runs on a more sophisticated control board than competing luxury ranges, reflects in parts cost); door hinge $345-$525; glass touch panel $485-$780. Outdoor side: GMWR outdoor refrigerator compressor work $585-$985, outdoor range igniter $245-$385 (heavier-spec than indoor for weather sealing). Parts ship through Hestan's US distribution, typically 5-10 day lead — faster than Italian-origin brands, slower than mass-market US brands like GE Appliances."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the most common Hestan failure pattern we see?",
    a: "The dominant pattern in our LA Hestan service mix is the <strong>2018-2021 GROR-series convection fan bearing</strong>. The GROR 30 / 36 / 48 ranges from this production window develop convection fan bearing wear around year 4 to 5, and the symptom catches owners off guard because it's quieter than they expect for a fan that size — a soft low-pitched hum or grinding at start-up that disappears once the fan is up to full speed, gradually getting louder over a 2-3 month window before the bearing fully fails. By the time most owners call us the fan has progressed to a clear grinding noise across the full convection cycle. Fix is convection fan motor replacement with OEM Hestan part ($345-$525 with labor), typically same-day if we have the GROR motor on the truck. Worth pairing with an inspection of the bake / broil element and oven thermostat at the same visit — the 2018-2021 cohort sometimes shows matched-cycle wear on adjacent components. Beyond that pattern, the other common Hestan service items are smart-platform connectivity issues (control board firmware or replacement, $385-$580) and the standard ceramic igniter and spark module wear on the gas burner side that any luxury cooking brand sees."
  },
  {
    q: "How does Hestan compare to Wolf?",
    a: "Honest comparison from servicing both regularly: Hestan and Wolf compete at the same price tier and similar build-quality philosophy, but they're philosophically different products. <strong>Wolf</strong> is sealed-burner sealed-system construction (Sub-Zero Group, Madison WI), dominant US distribution through authorized dealers, factory service network you can rely on across the country, parts ship through Sub-Zero's well-developed pipeline (typical 3-7 day). The Wolf service economics are well-understood — repair costs are predictable, parts are available, technicians trained on Wolf are common. <strong>Hestan</strong> is newer (residential lineup since 2015), smaller dealer network, smart-cooking platform built around connected-app control, hand-built construction with US parts supply via Hestan's own distribution (5-10 day typical). Repair costs run roughly comparable to Wolf at the major-component level; the smart-platform electronics on Hestan add a cost tier Wolf doesn't have because Wolf's controls are simpler and more mechanical. Longevity is similar between the two brands on the cooking surface (cast iron grates, brass valves), and similar on the oven side. The Hestan installations we see in Calabasas, Hidden Hills, and the design-forward neighborhoods were chosen specifically because the owner wanted something other than the default luxury brand — Hestan's smaller market share is part of why owners chose it."
  },
  {
    q: "How long do Hestan appliances last?",
    a: "Hestan residential appliances are designed for 20-25 year service life with normal use — comparable to Wolf, Sub-Zero, and Thermador on durability targets. Cast iron grates, brass valves, all-stainless construction, US-based factory build. The components that wear are predictable: ceramic igniters year 5-8 ($185-$285 per zone), spark modules year 4-6 ($265-$405), convection fan bearing year 4-5 on the 2018-2021 GROR cohort specifically ($345-$525), oven thermostat year 6-9 ($265-$405), HVBI blower motor year 8-12 ($385-$580). The smart-platform electronics are the newest variable in the longevity picture — Hestan's connected control boards have only been in the field since 2015, and we're starting to see year 8+ replacement cycles on first-generation boards. Cost-of-ownership is favorable: against $9,000-$18,000 replacement-unit pricing for new Hestan ranges (depending on configuration), a $400-$600 mid-life repair recovers 5-10 years of additional service. Custom-finish installations specifically favor repair over replacement — Hestan's color and trim options change between model years and exact-match replacement isn't always available."
  },
  {
    q: "Is Hestan made in the USA?",
    a: "Yes. Hestan residential appliances are designed and manufactured in California — the residential operation runs out of Anaheim, with the parent Hestan Commercial Corporation having been an Anaheim-based commercial cooking manufacturer since 1986. The residential brand (Hestan Smart Cooking) launched in 2015 as a consumer offshoot of the commercial heritage. Parts ship from US distribution rather than European supply chains, which translates to faster lead times than ILVE or Bertazzoni and comparable to Wolf or Sub-Zero. The American-made positioning is part of why some customers choose Hestan over Italian or German alternatives — and it's relevant to service economics, since parts don't carry a 14-21 day European-import wait."
  },
  {
    q: "Where can I find the official Hestan manual or warranty information?",
    a: `Our technicians work independently of Hestan's factory service network — we're often faster and available same-day across Southern California.`
  }
];

