<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01, About this service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Hestan is the newest luxury brand on our service list — Napa Valley founded 2015, hand-built — we see them in Calabasas and Hidden Hills kitchens where the owner wanted something nobody else has.</h2>

    <p>Hestan's residential cooking line launched in 2015 as the consumer offshoot of Hestan Commercial Corporation, an Anaheim-based commercial cooking manufacturer that has been supplying restaurants since 1986. The residential brand markets under "Hestan Smart Cooking" and runs a connected-app platform that integrates the cooktop, oven, ventilation, and outdoor cooking suite into a single controlled system. In our 5-county SoCal service mix, Hestan shows up in a specific demographic: Calabasas, Hidden Hills, and Sherman Oaks design-forward kitchens where the homeowner specifically wanted something other than the default Wolf or Thermador, plus the wealthier eastside neighborhoods (Los Feliz, Hancock Park, Larchmont) where the smart-platform integration was the deciding spec.</p>

    <p>Three Hestan-specific realities shape every service call. First, <strong>this is not a full-suite brand</strong>. Hestan residential covers cooking (indoor and outdoor ranges, cooktops), ventilation (HVBI hoods), and refrigeration columns plus outdoor refrigeration. There's no Hestan laundry. There's no Hestan dishwasher line of any size — when we see a Hestan kitchen, the dishwasher in the same kitchen is almost always Miele, Bosch, or KitchenAid. Owners scope kitchen suites accordingly. Second, <strong>the smart-platform electronics add a service tier other luxury brands don't have</strong>. Hestan's connected app control runs through a more sophisticated control board than Wolf or Thermador's relatively simple electronics, and connectivity issues (app pairing failures, firmware update problems, control board replacement) come up in 15-20% of our Hestan service calls. The platform is the brand's selling point and also its newest service variable — first-generation boards from 2015 are entering year-10 replacement cycles. Third, <strong>parts ship from US distribution out of Anaheim</strong>, typical 5-10 day lead time — faster than Italian-origin brands like ILVE or Bertazzoni (which carry 14-21 day European supply waits), slower than mass-market US brands like GE Appliances (2-5 day).</p>

    <p>Every Hestan service call gets a $89 residential diagnostic (applied toward the repair when work is approved), OEM Hestan parts, and an honest written quote before any work begins. We hold common GROR-series convection fan motors and ceramic igniters on the truck for the dominant 30 / 36 / 48-inch configurations — many service calls complete same-day.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 CATEGORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, Hestan repair categories</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Indoor cooking, outdoor cooking, ventilation, refrigeration.</h2>

    <div class="callout-box">
      <h3>2018-2021 GROR-series convection fan bearing pattern (most common Hestan service call)</h3>
      <p>The GROR 30 / 36 / 48 ranges manufactured between roughly 2018 and 2021 develop convection fan bearing wear around year 4 to 5. The symptom is quieter than expected for the fan size — a soft low-pitched hum or grinding at start-up that disappears once the fan is at full speed, gradually getting louder over a 2-3 month window before the bearing fully fails. By the time most owners call us, the grinding is audible across the full convection cycle. Fix is convection fan motor replacement with OEM Hestan part ($345-$525 with labor), <strong>typically same-day when we stock the GROR motor on the truck</strong> (we do for the dominant 36-inch configuration). Worth pairing with bake / broil element inspection and thermostat check at the same visit — the 2018-2021 cohort sometimes shows matched-cycle wear on adjacent oven components.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="appliance-grid">
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>GROR indoor ranges</h3>
        <p>30, 36, 48-inch dual-fuel and gas ranges. Open-burner / sealed-burner variants depending on configuration. Service tree: ceramic igniter ($185-$285), spark module ($265-$405), convection fan motor ($345-$525), oven thermostat ($265-$405), bake / broil element ($245-$385), smart-control board ($385-$580).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>HOTR outdoor ranges</h3>
        <p>Outdoor cooking ranges built for weather exposure — different sealing spec than indoor, different burner construction. Service items overlap with indoor (igniters, valves) but parts carry weather-rated upgrades. HOTR24 covers the 24-inch configuration common in our outdoor kitchen mix.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>GMWR outdoor refrigerators</h3>
        <p>Outdoor refrigeration units engineered for ambient temperatures up to 110°F (Hidden Hills and Calabasas summer pool decks routinely hit that envelope). Compressor and condenser fan service is the main wear category — outdoor units run harder than indoor refrigeration.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>HVBI ventilation hoods</h3>
        <p>Built-in ventilation hoods designed to match Hestan range collections. Blower motor ($385-$580), fan speed switch, light socket and bulb, damper assembly. Standard hood service tree with Hestan-specific parts supply.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Indoor refrigeration columns</h3>
        <p>Integrated column refrigerator and freezer units competing with Sub-Zero's column line. Compressor, evaporator fan, defrost timer, ice maker service. Newer to the lineup with lower LA service volume than the cooking side.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Smart-platform diagnostics</h3>
        <p>The Hestan connected app integration adds a service category competitors don't have. App pairing failures, firmware update issues, control board replacement on first-generation 2015-2018 platforms entering year-10 cycles. Diagnostic includes connectivity verification.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

